        <content><![CDATA[ <h1 class="title topictitle1">Breakdown sources</h1>  <div class="body conbody">  <p class="p"><span class="ph">A breakdown source specifies the elements that the breakdown            should contain.</span></p>  <p class="p"><span class="ph">Breakdown sources are based on a facts table that provides                breakdown elements, which are the groups that broken-down scores are organized by.                For example, a breakdown source might specify the choices from the                    <span class="ph uicontrol">Priority</span> choice list as the breakdown elements. Scores                broken down based on this breakdown source are then organized based on the                    <span class="ph uicontrol">Priority</span> value of each record. A breakdown source can be                shared by multiple breakdowns and indicators.</span></p> </div>]]></content>
